      "span_text": "The effect of G6PD on angiogenesis and tissue repair involves Flk-1, AKT, and Pim-1. However, pentose phosphate pathway was increased during PFKFB3 knockdown. Given this, PFKFB3 seems to not act through G6PD-associated pathway to alter endothelial angiogenesis, although PFKFB3 knockdown and G6PD deficiency share many similarities in the effect and mechanisms."
